 Dashboard UI Design Requirements Summary
🚀 New User Onboarding
Clear setup indicators - Show incomplete setup steps prominently
Popup checklist - Bubble.io-style onboarding flow
Primary action - Setup initial ICPs and prompts → start tracking
📊 Established User Dashboard
KPI Reports - Google Ads-style dashboard (up to 4 KPIs displayed)
Time-based metrics - Historical performance over time
Filtering system - Filter by specific ICP, change KPI selection
Opportunity pipeline - Interactive checklist with check-off and snooze functionality
🧭 Main Navigation Structure
ICPs & Prompts - Profile and prompt management
Performance - AI prompt monitoring results and analytics
Content Pipeline - Website audit + competitor benchmarking + content writer tools
Settings - API keys, billing, user preferences (accessible app-wide)
🎯 Key UX Patterns
Progressive disclosure - New users see setup, established users see analytics
Task-oriented design - Clear actionable items and completion tracking
Contextual access - Settings available throughout the application
Data-driven interface - Emphasis on metrics, filtering, and time-based reporting
📐 Design References
Onboarding: Bubble.io checklist popup
Analytics: Google Ads dashboard layout
Navigation: Module-based architecture with persistent settings access